author: Written by: FOX8Live.com Staff
title: Man found shot to death in parked car in Gibson
text:
GIBSON, LA (WVUE) - Terrebonne Parish deputies want to find out who shot and killed a Houma man in a car in Gibson Wednesday morning.
Sheriff Jerry Larpenter said that at approximately 9 a.m., deputies and detectives responded to a private driveway in the 4700 block of Bayou Black Dr. Gibson.
Investigators say the victim, Robert Dwayne Swan, 24, died of an apparent gun shot wound.
An autopsy is scheduled for Thursday morning.
Anyone with information concerning this investigation is asked to call the Terrebonne Parish Sheriffâ€™s Office, (985)876-2500, or Bayou Region Crime Stoppers, 1(800)743-7433, and may be eligible for a cash reward. The caller can remain anonymous and still receive a cash reward up to $1,000.00.
